HEADWORD: Unbegotten
<hw>Un`be*got"ten</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not +
<ets>begot</ets>, <ets>begotten</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not begot; not yet
generated; also, having never been generated; self-existent;
eternal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbeguile</ent>⟦br⟧
